OL,3,CUnited States kick off home World Cup
OL,4,Ccampaign with 4-1 win over Paraguay
OL,6,FThe United States have begun their
OL,7,FWorld Cup campaign with a historic 4-1
OL,8,Fwin against Paraguay.
OL,10,FThe US are currently co-hosting the
OL,11,F2026 FIFA World Cup, alongside Canada
OL,12,Fand Mexico, having last hosted in 1994.
OL,14,FPlaying at the SoFi Stadium in Los
OL,15,FAngeles on Friday, the US team had
OL,16,Fbuilt a 3-0 lead by halftime, with two
OL,17,Fof those goals being scored by striker
OL,18,FFolarin Balogun.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/7
